						<div class="postbody">I agree with the idea of multiple main loops (and even multiple NMIs) rather than only one loop with lots of branching.
<br />
<br />In my game, I have a main loop for each part, and each part can activate a different NMI routine. The simpler parts use a basic NMI handler that just signals the start of VBlank, but the main engine needs a custom, much more complex routine.</div>

