				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">For my game, I have a couple of main loops. But I access them all from a universal main loop:
<br />
<br />MainLoop:
<br /> jmp ($xxxx)
<br />LoopReturn:
<br /> inc LoopCount
<br /> lda vblCount
<br />-
<br /> cmp vblCount
<br /> beq -
<br /> jmp MainLoop
<br />
<br />
<br />I just stick whatever main loop address I want in RAM, and jump to that. Within my most frequently used main loop, I have one indirect jump like this which usually points to hardcoded routines for event handling.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/" class="postlink">-Owner of Poultry Games</a></div>
